I'm taking a wild guess that this message might refer to one that I
posted a few days back concerning problems with the Promise controller
and running the driver in 32bit mode. There was nothing quoted and no
message reference included in your post.

Anyway, I found that running the standard IBM driver when I only had 2
hard drives, running the Promise driver in both 16bit and 32bit mode
when I added the second 2 hard drives to the Promise card, didn't seem
to make much difference. In fact, at one time, I ran the Promise driver
in 16bit mode for almost a month because of forgetting to switch it back
after running Deskman/2 to back up my desktop, and I didn't even realize
it until next time I went to do a complete desktop backup and went to
change it to 16bit mode and discovered it was already in 16bit mode.

BTW, with the Buslogic card, I have my 4-540MB drives linked in 2 pairs
so that they appear as 2-1080MB drives. With this combination and using
the standard OS/2 driver I got about a 20% speed increase over the best
I ever got with the Promise card and driver. Using the Buslogic driver
gives me around a 50% speed increase over the Promise. BTW, both cards
had 4-1MB SIMMS for cache on them (in fact, it is the same SIMMS...I
just moved them over when I got the Buslogic card).

